Functions for isolating data in dplyr

  • dplyr 2 [<vector 1> , <vector 2>]
    • select(): data frame (variables) (i.e.columns of a data frame)
    • filter(): data frame (observations) (i.e.rows of a data frame)
    • select() filter() [<vector 1> , <vector 2>] vector 2 vector 1 dplyr arrange()

group_by(): 

pollution <- tibble::tribble(
       ~city,   ~size, ~amount, 
  "New York", "large",      23,
  "New York", "small",      14,
    "London", "large",      22,
    "London", "small",      16,
   "Beijing", "large",      121,
   "Beijing", "small",      56
)
pollution
#> # A tibble: 6 x 3
#>   city     size  amount
#>   <chr>    <chr>  <dbl>
#> 1 New York large     23
#> 2 New York small     14
#> 3 London   large     22
#> 4 London   small     16
#> 5 Beijing  large    121
#> 6 Beijing  small     56
pollution %>% 
  group_by(city) %>% 
    summarise(mean = mean(amount), 
              sum = sum(amount),
              count = n())
#> # A tibble: 3 x 4
#>   city      mean   sum count
#>   <chr>    <dbl> <dbl> <int>
#> 1 Beijing   88.5   177     2
#> 2 London    19      38     2
#> 3 New York  18.5    37     2

pollution city 3 3 ()
